trans-unit.source:
Volunteers for Salesforce supports Volunteer Recurrence Schedules and Job Recurrence Schedules with the help of a batch process to create future Shifts and assign volunteers to them. You can run this process manually, by clicking the Run Batch button, or you can schedule it to automatically run nightly.

You will see a progress bar below for the most recent batch process. The process may take some time; it will take longer the more data you have in your database. You can close this page and the process will continue in the background.

To view currently scheduled Jobs, go to the Scheduled Jobs page.

To schedule the Recurrence Schedules process to run automatically, go to the Schedule Apex Jobs page.
trans-unit.target: V4S assiste les calendriers de récurrence des bénévoles et les calendriers de récurrence de tâches à l’aide d’un processus par lot pour planifier des horaires de travail et leur assigner des bénévoles. Vous pouvez lancer ce processus manuellement, en cliquant sur le bouton Exécution de lot, ou vous pouvez planifier son exécution automatique chaque nuit.Vous verrez une barre de progression en dessous du processus par lot le plus récent. Il se peut que le processus prenne un certain temps, plus vous avez de données dans votre base de données plus le processus est long. Vous pouvez fermer cette page, le processus continuera en arrière-plan.Pour voir les tâches actuellement prévues, accédez à la <a href="/08e?setupid=ScheduledJobs">page des tâches prévues. Pour planifier l’exécution automatique du processus des calendriers de récurrence, accédez à la page de planification des tâches Apex.

The Welkin's Flow DataTable is a universal component that is able to display any records, however it could not accept Record Collection variables.

To display records in the component - you need to pass a Text Collection with their IDs.


This is why there is a separate loop in the flow to convert Record Collection to a Text Collection.

It is not possible to display all accounts in your Organization, so please enter the date that will be used to filter the Accounts list.

We will look for Accounts that were modified on or after the date below.
Please select up to 10 accounts to show their contacts. You can select records across multiple pages.

As you can see below - the DataTable component provides a lot of controls for your users:

  • They can sort using any column
  • They can search through the list of records
  • They have handy pagination options
  • etc.
The easiest way to start working with the Welkin's Flow DataTable is to create a new Flow using the bundled template.

The Welkin's Flow DataTable components allows you to specify some input parameters:

  • Collection to be shown
  • Comma-separated list of fields to be shown (you can even reference parent fields)
  • Maximal number of records that a user can select in the list
  • Minimal number of records that a user should select in the list before proceeding
  • Collection of pre-selected records
  • An option to show the component's embedded navigation footer (described later)

Welkin's DataTable for Flows also provides admins and developers a way to force users to select a certain amount of records. You can even disable the "Next" or "Proceed" buttons until a users selects the minimal number of records.


To provide such a validation capability - the component has it's own embedded Navigation footer, and it is shown, that replicates standard footer, but adds such a validation.


You can enforce users to select a minimal number of records doing the following steps:

  1. Specify a minimal number of records to be selected in the options section for the component.
  2. Disable the standard Screen Footer on the particular screen.
  3. Place the DataTable component at the bottom of the screen.
  4. Set the "Enable custom footer" to True.

It is important to mention that the built-in navigation footer competely replicates the standard one, and it also get all it's settings - you don't need to configure any

The Welkin's Flow DataTable components provides an option for you to allow your users to select certain records from the list.

You can select a Text Collection variable that will store IDs of selected records.
